    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS. This example features the sought-after 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a factory M-variable limited-slip differential. Technical highlights include a recently refreshed cooling system, reinforced rear subframe mounting points, and updated rod bearings for peace of mind. The chassis is supported by Bilstein dampers and refreshed bushings, maintaining the precise turn-in and telepathic steering feedback these cars are known for. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical components are robust, with a linear power band and a crisp 8,000 RPM redline. A true driver\u2019s spec with no mechanical compromises.",
